  "prompt": "What is the best iOS calendar app that allows you to cross off EVENTS as you go through the day?",
  "response": "After researching various iOS calendar apps, the best option that allows you to cross off events as you go through the day is the \"Structured - Daily Planner\" app. Here's why:\n\n1. **Event Crossing Off**: Structured allows you to mark events and tasks as completed by tapping on them, which visually crosses them off your schedule.\n\n2. **Intuitive Interface**: The app's design is clean and user-friendly, making it easy to manage your daily schedule.\n\n3. **Customization**: You can customize the look and feel of your calendar, including colors and icons for different types of events.\n\n4. **Integration**: It integrates well with the native iOS calendar, allowing you to import existing events.\n\n5. **Additional Features**: Structured also offers features like time blocking, reminders, and the ability to add notes to events.\n\nWhile there are other calendar apps available, Structured stands out for its specific feature of allowing you to cross off events, which can be very satisfying and helpful for tracking your progress throughout the day.\n\nYou can download Structured - Daily Planner from the App Store to try it out.",
